Confusing story #1: Analysis called this a blunder, but yet, 4...d6 5.d5 gives me further control and if 4..b5, I won't mind moving my Bishop to d3. If I played 4.Nxg5, sure, it would pin Black's pawn to his Queen, but like in the Damiano Defence, what is the logic of taking when it causes the loss of a win? Which side should I be more concerned about?
